#--------------------------------------------- #Main #based on MOB-D-017 V10 #Antony Brown 19 April 2018 #copyright Atlas Genetics Ltd 2018
#---------------------------------------------
#-------------Revision-History---------------- #Version 1.0 - Copied from MOB-D-019 V10 # - call MOB-EP-576_PCR_fill V9 AKA DPR PCR fill # - Increase PCR CYles to 42 cycles from MOB-D-014 V4.0 #Version 2.0 - MOB-CM-0176 #Version 3.0 - MOB-CM-0183 - CONCH 25 #Verison 4.0 - MOB-CM-0192 #---------------------------------------------
call MOB-D-049 #Progress Indicator NEW MOB-D-049 Version 1.0
call MOB-D-025 #Initialise Run MOB-D-025 Version 3.0
#Sample extract call MOB-D-026 #Lysis Release MOB-D-026 version 1.0 call MOB-D-027 #Mix MOB-D-027 version 3.0 call MOB-D-028 #Pump MOB-D-028 version 2.0 call MOB-D-020 #Air_purge_1 MOB-D-020 version 5.0 call MOB-D-029 #Wash Release MOB-D-029 version 2.0 call MOB-D-047 #air_dry_1min_750 MOB-D-047 version 2.0 call MOB-D-048 #elution_dispense_1min MOB-D-048 Version 1.0
#pcr and detection call MOB-D-023 #Homogenise MOB-D-023 version 3.0 call MOB-D-046 #PCR_DPR_Fill MOB-D-046 v1.0 call PAN-D-078 #UNG Step PAN-D-078 version 3.0 call MOB-D-045 #42 cycle Rapid PCR MOB-D-045 version 1.0 call MOB-D-022 #Fill Detection Chambers MOB-D-022 version 2.0 call MOB-D-050 #Detection Incubation NEW MOB-D-050 version 1.0
#setup peak search parameters and call voltammetry #peak algorithm "type" rawnoise permissible noise polyorder targetnoise peak algorithm "MultiPeak1Analysis" 1000 1000 6 49
#peak define "name" outcome ch vstart vend vexp vtol thresh maxnoise prop widthmax widthmin propnoise
peak define "CTIC" Positive 1 110 310 200 32 90 Infinity 25 60 160 90 4 peak define "CT" Positive 1 295 510 390 60 115 Infinity 25 60 160 90 4 peak define "clearend" Ignore 1 520 620 #this ignores the last part of the scan
peak define "NG1IC" Positive 3 110 310 200 32 90 Infinity 25 60 160 90 4 peak define "NG1" Positive 3 295 510 390 60 50 Infinity 25 60 160 90 4 peak define "clearend" Ignore 3 520 620 #this ignores the last part of the scan
peak define "NG2IC" Positive 4 110 310 200 32 60 Infinity 25 60 160 90 4 peak define "NG2" Positive 4 295 510 390 60 45 Infinity 25 60 160 90 4 peak define "clearend" Ignore 4 520 620 #this ignores the last part of the scan
call MOB-D-016 #Mob-D-016 Version 3.0 voltammetry

#--------------------------------------------- #NAT_CTNG_Volatmmetry #MOB-D-016 #Antony Brown 05 Oct 2016 #Copyright Atlas Genetics Ltd 2016 # #Initialed to verify that this is a copy of the master script # # # #---------------------------------------------
#-------------Revision-History---------------- #Version 1.0 - MOB-CM-0024 #version 2.0 - MOB-CM-0055 #version 3.0 - MOB-CM-0066 #---------------------------------------------
#syntax is start voltage mV, pulse amplitude mV, sweep increment mV, end voltage mV, pulse time ms, base time ms
throw 10002,99
#Data Scan voltammetry differential 0 50 3 600 40 60 delay 2200
throw 10002,100 #End process sequence - release pressure from bellows to waste begin atomic 1 #set starting valve conditions so flow through to waste valve v2 on valve v3 off valve v4 on valve v5 on valve v6 on valve v7 off valve v8 on
delay 30 valve v1 on
end

#--------------------------------------------- #NAT_CTNG_air_purge_1 #Mob-D-020 #Antony Brown 11 MAY 2017 #Copyright Atlas Genetics Ltd 2017 #---------------------------------------------
#-------------Revision-History---------------- #Version 1.0 - MOB-CM-0041 #Version 2.0 - MOB-CM-0055 #version 3.0 - MOB-CM-0108 #version 4.0 - MOB-CM-0113 #version 5.0 - MOB-CM-0125 #---------------------------------------------
#setup start conditions valve v1 off valve v2 off valve v3 on valve v4 on valve v5 on valve v6 on valve v7 off valve v8 on dpr dpr1 off delay 50
#check for res 3 charged if res2800 # do nothing else call error_30014 endif delay 10
#blow out back for 4.5s valve v9 on delay 10 valve v8 off valve v4 off delay 20
delay 450
#shutdown valve v8 on delay 10 valve v9 off delay 20 valve v4 on
#allow pressure to disapate. delay 100
#vent any remaining to sample well valve v3 off valve v2 off delay 30 valve v3 on delay 30 valve v4 on

#--------------------------------------------- #NAT_CTNG_fill_detection_chambers #MOB-D-022 #Antony Brown 19 July 2016 #Copyright Atlas Genetics Ltd 2016 # #Initialed to verify that this is a copy of the master script # # # #---------------------------------------------
#-------------Revision-History---------------- #Version 1.0 - MOB-CM-0041 #version 2.0 - MOB-CM-0055 #---------------------------------------------
#set starting valve conditions valve v1 off valve v2 on valve v3 on valve v4 on valve v5 on valve v6 on valve v7 on valve v8 on valve v16 off valve v17 on delay 10
#Set Pstat to internal circuit pstat 0 internal
#Engage mechanical valve stepper l5 200 300 # slow down mech valve to top of tpe delay 200 stepper l5 50 310 mechengage wait mechengage 5 delay 500
#set up DPR dpr dpr1 on 2 0 valve v16 on delay 10
#set up fill Detection chambers valve v2 off delay 10
begin atomic 8 valve v2 on delay 50 valve v2 off delay 50 end
#Fill dpr dpr1 on 28 900 delay 950 valve v2 on delay 50
#keep dpr on during reach and prtect instrument valve v17 off # protect instrument from potential back wash

#--------------------------------------------- #NAT_CTNG_homogenisation #MOB-D-023 #Antony Brown 11 MAY 2017 #Copyright Atlas Genetics Ltd 2017 #---------------------------------------------
#-------------Revision-History---------------- #Version 1.0 - MOB-CM-0041 #Version 2.0 - MOB-CM-0055 #Version 3.0 - MOB-CM-0125 #---------------------------------------------
begin atomic 1
#lift elution blister actuator stepper l2 500 -600 elutionlift wait elutionlift 5
#retract wash stepper stepper L4 200 -550 washretract wait washretract 15
#back off actuator from stop stepper l2 500 20 backoff stepper l4 500 20 backoffw wait backoff 2 wait backoffw 2
end
#set start conditions valve v1 off valve v2 off valve v3 on valve v4 on valve v5 on valve v6 on valve v7 off valve v8 on valve v17 on delay 10
#open to DPR dpr dpr1 on 5 0 delay 30 valve v16 on delay 20
#cycle between 1-5% atmospheric begin nonatomic 30 done valve v16 on delay 20 valve v16 off delay 20 end wait done 30 dpr dpr1 on 2 0

#--------------------------------------------- #NAT_CTNG_Initialise_Run #MOB-D-025 #Antony Brown 12 MAY 2017 #copyright Atlas Genetics Ltd 2017 #---------------------------------------------
#-------------Revision-History--------------- #version 1.0 - MOB-CM-0055 #version 2.0 - MOB-CM-0108 #Version 3.0 - MOB-CM-0125 #--------------------------------------------
#Set Pstat to internal circuit pstat 0 internal
begin atomic 1 done set Motor.Steppers.Pwm 100 #high force movements stepper l2 500 60 step stepper l4 500 60 stepwash wait step 1 wait stepwash 1 stepper l2 500 -50 step2 stepper l4 500 -50 stepwash2 wait step2 1 wait stepwash2 1 stepper l2 500 60 step stepper l4 500 60 stepwash wait step 1 wait stepwash 1 stepper l2 500 -50 step2 stepper l4 500 -50 stepwash2 wait step2 1 wait stepwash2 1 stepper l2 500 60 step stepper l4 500 60 stepwash wait step 1 wait stepwash 1 stepper l2 500 -50 step2 stepper l4 500 -50 stepwash2 wait step2 1 wait stepwash2 1
set Motor.Steppers.Pwm 70 #standard force movements
stepper l2 500 -70 done stepper l4 500 -70 done2 wait done 5 wait done2 5 stepper l2 500 20 done # reset to initial position stepper l4 500 20 done2 wait done 5 wait done2 5
end
res res1 dump res res2 dump res res3 dump
#set dpr off so that new one does not buzz whilst res 3 is empty dpr dpr1 off
solenoid m1 on #isolation_release on # isolation solenoid should be powered up indefinitely solenoid s1 off #drawer_catch off # drawer_catch should be left off normally
#pressure valves are rippled on-and-off valve v12 on #vacuum_enable on valve v13 on #Low_High_Pressure_Select on valve v1 on #bellows on valve v2 on #pump_V1_pcr on valve v3 on #pump_V2 on valve v4 on #V3_wash_inlet on valve v5 on #V4_elute_inlet on valve v6 on #V5_elute_enable on valve v7 on #v6_waste_enable on valve v8 on valve v9 on #wash_air_dry on valve v10 on #elute_air_dry on valve v14 on #low_pressure_dump on valve v15 on #high_pressure_dump on valve v16 on #digital_enable on valve v11 on #vacuum_dump on valve v17 on
delay 10
valve v12 off #vacuum_enable off valve v13 off #Low_High_Pressure_Select off valve v1 off #bellows off valve v2 off #pump_V1_pcr off valve v3 off #pump_V2 off valve v4 off #V3_wash_inlet off valve v5 off #V4_elute_inlet off valve v6 off #V5_elute_enable off valve v7 off #v6_waste_enable off valve v8 off #air_dry_enable off valve v9 off #wash_air_dry off valve v10 off #elute_air_dry off valve v14 off #low_pressure_dump off valve v15 off #high_pressure_dump off valve v16 off #digital_enable off valve v11 off #vacuum_dump off valve v17 off #digital_outlet atmospheric off
#open manifold with no pressure in reservoirs valve v13 on valve v12 on delay 50
#charge positive hard res res2 hold 900 1100 2 initpswID
#set up valve conditions to suck in fluid forming a meniscus in sample well inlet valve v2 on delay 50 valve v1 on delay 100 #allow bellows to close fully before closing v3 valve v3 on valve v4 on valve v5 on valve v6 on valve v7 on valve v8 on delay 20
#charge res3 atomicly to stop original DPR form buzzing begin atomic 1 res res3 hold 700 900 3 res2800 delay 300 wait res2800 5 end
#turn on Sample well peltier to get to temp before mix set Peltier.Lysis.Kp 500000 set Peltier.Lysis.Ki 500 set Peltier.Lysis.Kd 0 set Peltier.Lysis.TargetOffset 5
#Turn on sample well heater therm therm1 on 37 heatsample
#Charge vacuum logic pressure for a softer mixing process res res1 hold 500 700 2 initvswID wait initpswID 10 wait initvswID 10
#check for pressures if initpswID #do nothing else call error_30010 endif if initvswID #do nothing else call error_30011 endif
#remove meniscus from sample well inlet with bellows valve v1 off delay 50 valve v2 off delay 2000
#Rattle bellows to remove any remaining meniscus begin nonatomic 2 done valve v1 on delay 40 valve v1 off delay 100 end
#relax reservoir to allow to recharge to gentle pressure for mix. res res2 dump delay 100 res res2 hold 400 550 2 initpswID wait initpswID 10

#--------------------------------------------- #NAT_CTNG_Lysis_Release #MOB-D-026 #Antony Brown 28 July 2016 #copyright Atlas Genetics Ltd 2016 # #Initialed to verify that this is a copy of the master script # # # #---------------------------------------------
#-------------Revision-History--------------- #version 1.0 - MOB-CM-0055 #--------------------------------------------
#set start conditions to check manifold protection valve v1 off valve v2 off valve v3 on valve v4 on valve v5 on valve v6 on valve v7 on valve v8 on
#Reach blister stepper l3 500 250 lysisreach1 wait lysisreach1 3
#crush blister slow and totally stepper l3 100 340 lysissquash
delay 370

#--------------------------------------------- #NAT_CTNG_Mix #MOB-D-027 #Antony Brown 11 Jan 2017 #copyright Atlas Genetics Ltd 2017 # #Initialed to verify that this is a copy of the master script # # # #---------------------------------------------
#-------------Revision-History--------------- #version 1.0 - MOB-CM-0055 #version 2.0 - MOB-CM-0066 #version 3.0 - MOB-CM-0108 #--------------------------------------------
wait heatsample 30 # only needs this long if it starts from warm. if heatsample #do nothing else call error_30013 endif
#set PID for sample well heater to stop control loop ringing therm therm1 off set Peltier.Lysis.Kp 350000 set Peltier.Lysis.Ki 15 therm therm1 on 37 ackvar
#Set up the fluidic path valve v1 off valve v2 off valve v3 on valve v4 on valve v5 on valve v6 on valve v7 on valve v8 on
begin atomic 1 #back off lysis actuator to protect manifold from leaking. stepper l3 500 -400 lysisretract wait lysisretract 5 end
#mix fluid # v1 bellows off and on in that order to keep as much sample as possible over heater begin nonatomic 11 ACK # 11 cycles as first on is a false pump valve v1 off delay 100 valve v1 on delay 100 #back gulp 2.8seconds valve v2 on delay 30 valve v3 off delay 30 valve v1 off delay 100 valve v3 on delay 30 valve v2 off delay 30 valve v1 on delay 60 #extra delay to evenly space 11 pumps over 1 min (cycle time = 4.8s) delay 65 end wait ACK 25
#turn off sample well heater therm therm1 off
#return positive logic to normal operational pressure res res2 hold 1100 1250 2 initpswID wait initpswID 10 if initpswID # leave blank to leave visual marker in script. else call error_30010 endif

#--------------------------------------------- #NAT_CTNG_Pump #MOB-D-028 #Antony Brown 11 Jan 2017 #copyright Atlas Genetics Ltd 2017 # #Initialed to verify that this is a copy of the master script # # # #---------------------------------------------
#-------------Revision-History--------------- #version 1.0 - MOB-CM-0055 #version 2.0 - MOB-CM-0108 #--------------------------------------------
#Prime_to_pump_to_waste: sets up the fluidic path valve v1 on valve v2 off valve v3 on valve v4 on valve v5 on valve v6 on valve v7 off valve v8 on
#pumps fluid begin nonatomic 12 pumped valve v3 on delay 5 valve v2 off delay 5 valve v1 off delay 100 valve v2 on delay 5 valve v3 off delay 5 valve v1 on delay 200 valve v1 off delay 30 valve v1 on delay 200 end wait pumped 25

#--------------------------------------------- #NAT_CTNG_Wash_Release #MOB-D-029 #Antony Brown 05 Spet 2016 #copyright Atlas Genetics Ltd 2016 # #Initialed to verify that this is a copy of the master script # # # #---------------------------------------------
#-------------Revision-History--------------- #version 1.0 - MOB-CM-0055 #Version 2.0 - MOB-CM-0066 #--------------------------------------------
#set start conditions to check manifold protection valve v1 off valve v2 on valve v3 on valve v4 off valve v5 on valve v6 on valve v7 off valve v8 on delay 50
#crush blister slow stepper l4 250 230 washreach1 wait washreach1 15 delay 10
#begin repeatedly crushing slightly then releasing back pressure until a displacment on 480 steps is reached begin nonatomic 12 stepper l4 100 40 washsquash wait washsquash 3 delay 140 end
#leave stepper down to stop blister inflating during air purges

#--------------------------------------------- #NAT_CTNG_42_Cycle_Rapid PCR #MOB-D-045 #Antony Brown 30 Apr 2018 #copyright Atlas Genetics Ltd 2018 # #Initialed to verify that this is a copy of the master script # # # #---------------------------------------------
#-------------Revision-History---------------- #version 1.0 - MOB-CM-0176 #---------------------------------------------
#Set up PCR peltier PID set Peltier.Pcr.Kp 600000 set Peltier.Pcr.Ki 10 set Peltier.Pcr.Kd 12000000 set Peltier.Pcr.Imax 120000
begin atomic 41 all_done #41 cycles starting from annealing to add in commands to run parrallel to save time in assay
#anneal #use accuracy-optimised parameters to return at 50% power. set Peltier.Pcr.Kp 400000 set Peltier.Pcr.Ki 0 set Peltier.Pcr.Kd 8000000 set Peltier.Pcr.Imax 50 set Peltier.Pcr.PwmMax 50 therm therm2 on 65 anneal wait anneal 15 if anneal #do nothing else call error_30018 endif delay 715
#extend #using re-optimised values to accurately edge up. set Peltier.Pcr.Kp 600000 set Peltier.Pcr.Ki 50 set Peltier.Pcr.Kd 10000000 set Peltier.Pcr.Imax 120 set Peltier.Pcr.PwmMax 50 therm therm2 on 65.8 adjust delay 200 therm therm2 on 66.8 phase3 delay 200 therm therm2 on 67.8 phase4 delay 100 therm therm2 on 69.0 phase5 delay 100 therm therm2 on 70.2 phase6 delay 200
#denature using original setting set Peltier.Pcr.Kp 600000 set Peltier.Pcr.Ki 10 set Peltier.Pcr.Kd 12000000 set Peltier.Pcr.Imax 120000 set Peltier.Pcr.PwmMax 50 therm therm2 on 98 phase1 wait phase1 6 delay 230 end wait all_done 1400
#final anneal at end of 41 cycles # to make up to 42 cycles and to preheat detection peltier.
#use accuracy-optimised parameters to return at 50% power. set Peltier.Pcr.Kp 400000 set Peltier.Pcr.Ki 0 set Peltier.Pcr.Kd 8000000 set Peltier.Pcr.Imax 50 set Peltier.Pcr.PwmMax 50 therm therm2 on 65 anneal wait anneal 15 if anneal #do nothing else call error_30018 endif delay 715
#-------------------------------------------- # preheat Detection peltier #using accuracy amended parameters begin atomic 1 set Peltier.Detection.Kp 255000 set Peltier.Detection.Ki 16 set Peltier.Detection.Kd 100000
therm therm3 on 42 preheatdetection delay 1000 # to equalise temperature wait preheatdetection 15 if preheatdetection #do nothing else call error_30016 endif end #-------------------------------------------
#extend #using re-optimised values to accurately edge up. set Peltier.Pcr.Kp 600000 set Peltier.Pcr.Ki 50 set Peltier.Pcr.Kd 10000000 set Peltier.Pcr.Imax 120 set Peltier.Pcr.PwmMax 50 therm therm2 on 65.8 adjust delay 200 therm therm2 on 66.8 phase3 delay 200 therm therm2 on 67.8 phase4 delay 100 therm therm2 on 69.0 phase5 delay 100 therm therm2 on 70.2 phase6 delay 200
#equalise temperature through cartridge use anneal PIDs set Peltier.Pcr.Kp 300000 set Peltier.Pcr.Ki 5 set Peltier.Pcr.Kd 0 set Peltier.Pcr.Imax 120000 set Peltier.Pcr.PwmMax 50
therm therm2 on 42 PCR42 wait PCR42 12 if PCR42 #do nothing else call error_30015 endif

#--------------------------------------------- #NAT_CTNG_PCR_DPR_fill #MOB-D-045 #Antony Brown 30 Apr 2018 #copyright Atlas Genetics Ltd 2018 # #Initialed to verify that this is a copy of the master script # # # #---------------------------------------------
#-------------Revision-History---------------- #version 1.0 - MOB-CM-0176 #---------------------------------------------
#Set start conditions valve v1 off valve v2 off valve v3 on valve v4 on valve v5 on valve v6 on valve v7 on valve v8 on valve v16 on
#Set DPR to on and fill to 19% atmospheric and saturate first spot for 10 secs to rehydrate dpr dpr1 on 19 300 delay 1330
# flux 5 times to disturb lifted reagent begin nonatomic 5 dpr dpr1 on 14 5 delay 50 dpr dpr1 on 17 5 delay 50 end
#Saturate second spot for 10 secs to rehydrate dpr dpr1 on 32 30 delay 1000
# flux 8 times over the 2nd spot begin nonatomic 8 dpr dpr1 on 23 5 delay 50 dpr dpr1 on 29 5 delay 50 end
#Retract to spread mix across chamber dpr dpr1 on 23 200 delay 500
#fill PCR chambers and finish sequence dpr dpr1 on 34 300 delay 300 valve v2 on delay 30
set Motor.Steppers.Pwm 100 #allow 100% current just for this move.
#Shut down DPR valve valve v16 off dpr dpr1 off delay 20
#Lift mechanical valve for PCR stepper l5 350 -900 liftMV delay 250 wait liftMV 5
stepper l5 350 20 # move mechnical valve off its stop set Motor.Steppers.Pwm 70

#--------------------------------------------- # NAT_CTNG_air_dry_1min_750 #MOB-D-047 #Antony Brown 06 Aug 2018 #copyright Atlas Genetics Ltd 2018 #---------------------------------------------
#-------------Revision-History---------------- #Version 1.0 - MOB-CM-0183 #Version 2.0 - MOB-CM-0192 #---------------------------------------------
#setup start conditions valve v1 off valve v3 on valve v2 off valve v4 on valve v5 on valve v6 on valve v7 off valve v8 on valve v16 off valve v17 off
#clear wash downstream from blister for 2 seconds to remove excess wash from upstream valve v9 on delay 20 valve v8 off valve v4 off delay 200 valve v8 on
#short pressure release delay 200
# blow again to displace extra wash fluid. valve v8 off delay 500 valve v8 on delay 25 valve v4 on delay 25 valve v9 off delay 30
#clear wash back to sample well prep for air dry for 0.2s to clear any excess between valves 3 and 4 valve v3 off delay 100 #disapate pressure valve v10 on delay 30 valve v8 off delay 30 valve v5 off #This is the period that the air flows to sample well delay 20 valve v3 on
#charge res2 higher to maintain valve seal during airdry res res2 hold 1200 1350 20 res21200 wait res21200 5 if res21200 #do nothing else call error_30010 endif
#airdry set up higher pressure res res3 hold 700 800 10 res31000
#airdry start delay 4000
#start peltier during airdry to preheat back end begin atomic 1 preheat set Peltier.Pcr.Kp 300000 set Peltier.Pcr.Ki 10 set Peltier.Pcr.Kd 0 set Peltier.Pcr.MinTemp 10 set Peltier.Pcr.Imax 120000
set Peltier.Detection.Kp 100000 set Peltier.Detection.Ki 10 set Peltier.Detection.Kd 0
therm therm3 on 22 cooldc therm therm2 on 37 warmstart wait cooldc 10 wait warmstart 10 end
#finish airdry delay 2000 valve v8 on delay 20
#check high pressure reservoir is able to hold pressure retrospectivly wait res31000 5 if res31000 #do nothing else call error_30014 endif
begin atomic 1 complete #lift lysis stepper motor stepper L3 200 -200 lysisretract wait lysisretract 5 end
#dump res3 after airdry and close air dry line res res3 dump delay 200 valve v10 off
#stop DPR buzzing during elute phase, favouring the new DPR dpr dpr1 off #res3 charge happens in elution dispence phase immediatly after this script
#set res 2 to lower valve logic pressure back to normal in due course res res2 hold 900 1100 3

#--------------------------------------------- #NAT_CTNG_elution_dispense_1min #MOB-D-048 #Antony Brown 08 June 2018 #copyright Atlas Genetics Ltd 2018 #---------------------------------------------
#set start conditions to check manifold protection valve v1 off valve v2 off valve v3 on valve v4 on valve v5 off valve v6 off valve v7 on valve v8 on valve v16 off #set valve v16 to vent elution well valve v17 on
begin atomic 1 #Charge Reservoir dpr dpr1 off delay 50 res res3 hold 700 900 3 initregID wait initregID 5 if initregID #do nothing else call error_30014 endif end
#engage menchanical valve stepper l5 500 600 mechvengage wait mechvengage 15 delay 125
#reach blister elution stepper L2 500 200 elutionreach1 wait elutionreach1 15
begin atomic 1 #check peltier is preheated
#PCR check if warmstart #do nothing else call error_30015 endif end
begin nonatomic 2 #2 steps to pop blister and cover column stepper L2 50 42 elutionsquash wait elutionsquash 3 delay 200 end
#delay 1 min delay 6000
begin nonatomic 8 #8 slow steps dispence eluate over column and into elution well stepper L2 50 50 elutionsquash wait elutionsquash 3 delay 200 end
#shutdown valve v6 on delay 100

#--------------------------------------------- #NAT_CTNG_Detection_Incubation_NEW #MOB-D-050 #Antony Brown 06 Aug 2018 #copyright Atlas Genetics Ltd 2018 # #Initialed to verify that this is a copy of the master script # # # #---------------------------------------------
#-------------Revision-History---------------- #Version 1.0 - MOB-CM-0192 #---------------------------------------------
begin atomic 1 delay 1963 throw 10002,90 delay 1963 throw 10002,91 delay 1963 throw 10002,92 delay 1963 throw 10002,93 delay 1963 throw 10002,94 delay 1963 throw 10002,95 delay 1963 throw 10002,96 delay 1963 throw 10002,97 delay 1963 throw 10002,98
end
#set incubation temperature therm therm3 on 37 INCDT
set peltier.pcr.ki 20 therm therm2 on 37 INCPCR wait INCPCR 30 wait INCDT 30
if INCDT #do nothing else call error_30016 endif
